My team has been writing its own vision system for a while that we run on a coprocessor, and after updating the WPILib libraries that we use to 2023’s, we are seeing an error when trying to connect to network tables. We’ve tried both 2023.1.1 and 2023.2.1 and see the same error message for each one.

Here’s what we see in the output just before it crashes:

NT: starting network client
/usr/bin/java: symbol lookup error: /root/.wpilib/nativecache/linux/x86-64/libntcorejni.so.4646d455f80d2f18ea5fdcf34271bfb1: undefined symbol: _ZN3wpi6detail18PromiseFactoryBase13CreateRequestEv

Has anyone seen anything similar? We are running on Linux on an x64 processor. This repros on two different machines that were set up basically the same way. When running the same app on Windows it doesn’t hit this error, which makes me think that there’s something special about linux x86_64.

We use the following in our build.gradle to pull in WPI dependencies (wpiVersion is 2023.2.1, platform is linuxx86-64):
implementation “edu.wpi.first.wpiutil:wpiutil-java:” + wpiVersion
implementation “edu.wpi.first.wpiutil:wpiutil-jni:” + wpiVersion + “:” + platform
implementation “edu.wpi.first.ntcore:ntcore-java:” + wpiVersion
implementation “edu.wpi.first.ntcore:ntcore-jni:” + wpiVersion + “:” + platform
implementation “edu.wpi.first.cscore:cscore-java:” + wpiVersion
implementation “edu.wpi.first.cscore:cscore-jni:” + wpiVersion + “:” + platform
implementation “edu.wpi.first.cameraserver:cameraserver-java:” + wpiVersion

Thanks!
